1
00:01:28,068 --> 00:01:30,036
Aah!

2
00:01:34,741 --> 00:01:37,938
Wait a minute.
He ain't dead!

3
00:01:46,086 --> 00:01:48,020
Let's go!
Let's go!

4
00:02:07,841 --> 00:02:08,933
Frank!

5
00:02:19,553 --> 00:02:20,986
Come on, Frank.

6
00:02:30,330 --> 00:02:32,264
Let's get the hell out!

7
00:02:35,735 --> 00:02:37,327
Frank!

8
00:02:37,404 --> 00:02:39,133
Frank!

9
00:02:46,379 --> 00:02:49,143
Frank!

10
00:02:54,754 --> 00:02:56,984
Frank!

11
00:02:57,057 --> 00:02:58,524
Hey, come back!

12
00:03:15,175 --> 00:03:17,609
But on this joyous day,

13
00:03:17,677 --> 00:03:20,111
one sobering question,
one haunting question remains.

14
00:03:20,213 --> 00:03:22,147
Are they all back?

15
00:03:22,215 --> 00:03:25,150
Still listed as
missing in action

16
00:03:25,218 --> 00:03:27,152
are 2,500 American men.

17
00:03:27,220 --> 00:03:31,156
Are any of them
still being held prisoner?

18
00:03:31,224 --> 00:03:33,351
For the families
of those men,

19
00:03:33,426 --> 00:03:36,156
the Vietnamese war
will never be over

20
00:03:36,229 --> 00:03:40,131
until that question
is answered.

21
00:03:40,200 --> 00:03:43,135
We're waiting
for the first P.O.W.

22
00:03:43,203 --> 00:03:45,137
to emerge from the plane.

23
00:03:45,205 --> 00:03:47,139
All of America waiting,

24
00:03:47,207 --> 00:03:50,142
and in particular,
his family is waiting.

25
00:03:50,210 --> 00:03:53,145
We'll see these heroes
emerging momentarily.

26
00:03:53,246 --> 00:03:57,683
We're waiting now for,
on this momentous day,

27
00:03:57,751 --> 00:04:01,619
the end of the war
officially fo rthem.

28
00:04:01,688 --> 00:04:03,622
This day, March 7, 1973.

29
00:04:03,690 --> 00:04:06,625
The first one
coming off now!

30
00:04:06,693 --> 00:04:08,593
He looks a little thin,

31
00:04:08,662 --> 00:04:11,096
but considering what
he's been through,

32
00:04:11,164 --> 00:04:14,099
he looks very good
from here.

33
00:04:14,167 --> 00:04:16,601
He's approaching
his family now.

34
00:04:16,670 --> 00:04:20,106
We're waiting
for others to come off.

35
00:04:20,173 --> 00:04:22,573
There's the official reunion.

36
00:04:22,642 --> 00:04:25,110
The war is over for him.

37
00:04:25,178 --> 00:04:28,715
For other American families,
the agonizing will continue

38
00:04:28,715 --> 00:04:29,079
For other American families,
the agonizing will continue

39
00:04:29,149 --> 00:04:34,951
until they find out
the fate of their missing sons.

40
00:04:35,021 --> 00:04:36,579
[Thunder]

41
00:04:36,656 --> 00:04:38,089
Daddy!

42
00:04:43,129 --> 00:04:44,061
Daddy.

43
00:04:47,500 --> 00:04:48,933
l'm scared.

44
00:04:49,002 --> 00:04:51,937
Can I sleep
with you tonight?

45
00:05:38,652 --> 00:05:40,586
Colonel Rhodes,
I sympathize, but--

46
00:05:40,654 --> 00:05:42,588
I don't want
your sympathy!

47
00:05:42,656 --> 00:05:45,591
I want you to help me
find my son.

48
00:05:45,659 --> 00:05:47,058
But don't you understand?

49
00:05:47,127 --> 00:05:48,560
There's nothing I can do.

50
00:05:48,628 --> 00:05:51,062
There are 2,500 men
still unaccounted for.

51
00:05:51,131 --> 00:05:53,065
There have been over
400 live sightings

52
00:05:53,133 --> 00:05:55,101
of Americans held
against their will.

53
00:05:55,168 --> 00:05:57,102
There's nothing I can do.

54
00:05:57,170 --> 00:05:59,604
That's all I ever
heard in Washington.

55
00:05:59,673 --> 00:06:01,038
Nobody can do anything.

56
00:06:01,107 --> 00:06:03,041
That's why I came
to Bangkok.

57
00:06:03,109 --> 00:06:05,543
Look, you didn't
hear this from me,

58
00:06:05,612 --> 00:06:08,547
but there are a couple
of men here in Bangkok

59
00:06:08,615 --> 00:06:12,483
who claim they've seen
American P.O.W.s in Laos.

60
00:06:14,120 --> 00:06:17,283
I think my son's being
held prisoner in Laos,

61
00:06:17,357 --> 00:06:18,790
but I need proof.

62
00:06:18,858 --> 00:06:21,759
Get my son's signature
on the back of this picture.

63
00:06:21,828 --> 00:06:25,525
Get my son's signature
on the back of that picture.

64
00:06:25,598 --> 00:06:27,031
All right?

65
00:06:29,135 --> 00:06:32,070
If I get your son's name here,

66
00:06:32,138 --> 00:06:34,971
I want lots of money.

67
00:06:35,041 --> 00:06:37,305
Yeah, O.K.

68
00:06:49,155 --> 00:06:50,588
Hey, you.

69
00:06:50,657 --> 00:06:52,591
[Speaking Thai]

70
00:07:08,775 --> 00:07:09,867
O.K.

71
00:07:13,780 --> 00:07:14,712
Hey!

72
00:07:22,122 --> 00:07:26,058
Oh, boy. There's that old
Colonel M.I.A. again.

73
00:07:26,126 --> 00:07:27,525
Hello, Colonel.

74
00:07:27,594 --> 00:07:29,027
How are you?

75
00:07:29,095 --> 00:07:32,030
Sorry we haven't
got time today,

76
00:07:32,098 --> 00:07:36,057
but give me a ring
in my office.

77
00:07:36,136 --> 00:07:37,569
Sorry.

78
00:07:40,507 --> 00:07:43,806
Colonel Rhodes,
I can't help you with your son.

79
00:07:43,877 --> 00:07:46,812
I'm trying to find food
for these new refugees.

80
00:07:46,880 --> 00:07:49,314
Talk to that guy over there.
He'll help.

81
00:07:49,382 --> 00:07:50,849
Thank you very much.

82
00:08:10,103 --> 00:08:11,536
That your boy.

83
00:08:11,604 --> 00:08:14,539
He prisoner in camp in Laos.

84
00:08:14,607 --> 00:08:17,542
I smuggled the picture out.

85
00:08:37,597 --> 00:08:40,532
I know my son's being held
somep lace in Northern Laos,

86
00:08:40,633 --> 00:08:43,067
but I need to know
exactly where.

87
00:08:43,136 --> 00:08:44,737
I need a thorough recon
of the area.

88
00:08:44,737 --> 00:08:45,533
I need a thorough recon
of the area.

89
00:08:45,605 --> 00:08:49,541
I can go into Laos
and North Vietnam.

90
00:08:49,609 --> 00:08:51,543
I've got the connections.

91
00:08:51,611 --> 00:08:56,446
But it'll take a lot of money
to find your son.

92
00:08:57,617 --> 00:08:58,549
Don, hi!

93
00:08:58,651 --> 00:09:00,585
How are you,Jason?

94
00:09:00,653 --> 00:09:03,121
What do you have for me?

95
00:09:03,189 --> 00:09:06,124
You know...ifthey
find out about this,

96
00:09:06,192 --> 00:09:08,592
they'll retire me,
just like they retired you.

97
00:09:08,661 --> 00:09:10,094
Yeah, yeah, O.K.

98
00:09:15,068 --> 00:09:18,504
I suppose someone
could call this treason.

99
00:09:20,073 --> 00:09:21,506
No. No, thanks.

100
00:09:24,077 --> 00:09:27,069
It's a prison camp in Laos.

101
00:09:27,146 --> 00:09:29,512
Look at the paddy dikes.

102
00:09:32,118 --> 00:09:34,052
There's your proof,Jason.

103
00:09:34,120 --> 00:09:36,054
There's your proof--111 .

104
00:09:36,122 --> 00:09:38,056
Go get your boy.

105
00:09:46,099 --> 00:09:47,031
O.K.

106
00:09:53,373 --> 00:09:55,034
Now, where was I?

107
00:09:55,108 --> 00:09:56,541
Hey, Blaster.

108
00:09:56,609 --> 00:09:59,544
Tell us about
that big wave.

109
00:09:59,612 --> 00:10:03,048
I've told you guys
that story a thousand times.

110
00:10:03,116 --> 00:10:06,381
I don't remember how I lied
the last time.

111
00:10:06,486 --> 00:10:09,421
It doesn't matter.
It's still going to be bitchin'.

112
00:10:09,489 --> 00:10:11,047
All right, all right.

113
00:10:11,157 --> 00:10:14,058
The surf on
the north shore

114
00:10:14,127 --> 00:10:15,594
comes up real fast.

115
00:10:15,695 --> 00:10:18,562
You're out there
having fun,

116
00:10:18,631 --> 00:10:20,565
and then it happens--

117
00:10:20,633 --> 00:10:22,567
a life-threatening
experience.

118
00:10:23,970 --> 00:10:25,403
And then?

119
00:10:26,873 --> 00:10:28,568
This photograph
was taken

120
00:10:28,641 --> 00:10:31,576
somewhere close
to where Frank is being held.

121
00:10:31,644 --> 00:10:34,078
I'm not saying
Frank is one of them,

122
00:10:34,147 --> 00:10:36,081
but those two
are Americans.

123
00:10:36,149 --> 00:10:38,583
They're much too tall
to be Vietnamese.

124
00:10:38,685 --> 00:10:41,119
Average Vietnamese man
is about 5'2-1 /2".

125
00:10:41,187 --> 00:10:44,122
And that's supposed
to be Frank?

126
00:10:44,190 --> 00:10:45,418
That is Frank.

127
00:10:45,491 --> 00:10:49,086
I bought too many fakes
over the last 10 years.

128
00:10:49,162 --> 00:10:50,595
That definitely is Frank.

129
00:10:50,663 --> 00:10:54,599
Been a P.O.W.
10 years in that shit hole?

130
00:10:54,667 --> 00:10:56,100
Frank is alive.

131
00:10:56,169 --> 00:10:57,602
You got that?

132
00:10:57,670 --> 00:10:59,604
My son is alive.

133
00:10:59,672 --> 00:11:02,038
Take a look at that.

134
00:11:02,108 --> 00:11:04,542
That's a high altitude
photograph

135
00:11:04,610 --> 00:11:06,544
taken from a SR-71 .

136
00:11:06,612 --> 00:11:08,045
Look closely.

137
00:11:09,615 --> 00:11:12,049
Look at the paddy dikes.

138
00:11:14,687 --> 00:11:16,382
The three lines there.

139
00:11:17,824 --> 00:11:19,086
111 .

140
00:11:20,960 --> 00:11:23,554
That's your old
LRRP team designation--

141
00:11:23,629 --> 00:11:25,563
First Battalion,
11 th Infantry.

142
00:11:25,631 --> 00:11:27,565
Don't you see it?

143
00:11:27,633 --> 00:11:29,066
Right here.

144
00:11:29,135 --> 00:11:30,227
Yes.

145
00:11:30,303 --> 00:11:32,567
That's three lines
in the ground.

146
00:11:32,638 --> 00:11:35,072
It could be anything.

147
00:11:35,141 --> 00:11:38,577
You know it isn't though,
don't you?

148
00:11:40,146 --> 00:11:43,081
That's a message
from my son.

149
00:11:44,650 --> 00:11:46,083
You know that.

150
00:12:01,768 --> 00:12:02,700
Hello.

151
00:12:04,103 --> 00:12:05,195
Hi.

152
00:12:05,271 --> 00:12:06,704
Mrs. Wilkes?

153
00:12:06,773 --> 00:12:08,206
Yeah, that's right.

154
00:12:09,675 --> 00:12:11,108
I'm Jason Rhodes.

155
00:12:11,177 --> 00:12:12,610
I phoned this morning.

156
00:12:12,678 --> 00:12:15,112
Yeah, I know who you are.

157
00:12:15,181 --> 00:12:18,116
Listen, my husband doesn't
want to talk to you.

158
00:12:18,184 --> 00:12:21,642
I phoned him this morning,
and he said he did.

159
00:12:21,721 --> 00:12:22,688
Not anymore.

160
00:12:22,789 --> 00:12:26,657
Why don't you
do me a favor and go away?

161
00:12:26,726 --> 00:12:29,627
Not until
I see your husband.

162
00:12:29,695 --> 00:12:32,129
You've got no right
to be here.

163
00:12:32,198 --> 00:12:34,132
It's taken me 1 0 years

164
00:12:34,200 --> 00:12:37,795
to get that god damned war
out of his head.

165
00:12:37,870 --> 00:12:41,033
Looks to me like
it's still in his head.

166
00:12:41,107 --> 00:12:42,802
Ohh...

167
00:12:42,875 --> 00:12:44,308
that's very deep.

168
00:12:44,377 --> 00:12:46,709
Where were you
all the days

169
00:12:46,779 --> 00:12:49,179
he spent staring
at the walls?

170
00:12:50,983 --> 00:12:51,915
Hey, Wilkes!

171
00:12:51,984 --> 00:12:52,916
Goddamn you!

172
00:12:53,019 --> 00:12:55,579
Why did you send
your wife out here?

173
00:12:55,688 --> 00:12:57,815
Don't you have
the guts to come out?

174
00:12:57,924 --> 00:12:59,357
Leave him alone!

175
00:12:59,425 --> 00:13:01,256
My son needs you!

176
00:13:01,327 --> 00:13:04,262
At least look
at our photographs.

177
00:13:08,835 --> 00:13:10,268
Wilkesy.

178
00:13:10,336 --> 00:13:12,770
I'll handle this now.

179
00:13:23,316 --> 00:13:25,784
I don't like your tactics.

180
00:13:25,885 --> 00:13:28,820
But I'll listen
because of Frank.

181
00:13:28,888 --> 00:13:29,820
O.K.

182
00:13:31,891 --> 00:13:32,823
Blaster.

183
00:13:34,861 --> 00:13:36,294
Wilkesy.

184
00:13:36,362 --> 00:13:39,297
Why didn't you
stay in touch?

185
00:13:39,365 --> 00:13:40,798
Why didn't you?

186
00:13:42,869 --> 00:13:44,302
I don't know.

187
00:13:44,370 --> 00:13:46,304
It's weird, ain't it?

188
00:13:48,374 --> 00:13:50,808
How did they find you?

189
00:13:50,877 --> 00:13:52,310
I don't know.

190
00:13:52,378 --> 00:13:54,812
Came looking
and found me.

191
00:13:54,881 --> 00:13:56,815
Then we found you.

192
00:13:56,883 --> 00:13:58,817
Thanks a lot, Blast.

193
00:13:58,918 --> 00:14:01,785
It's good
to see you, man.

194
00:14:34,720 --> 00:14:38,281
There are compounds
all over Northern Laos.

195
00:14:38,391 --> 00:14:40,825
There are choppers
we left behind.

196
00:14:40,860 --> 00:14:43,795
We'll use them to get
into the P.O.W. camp.

197
00:14:43,863 --> 00:14:45,797
They're used all the time,

198
00:14:45,865 --> 00:14:47,799
so they should be
well maintained.

199
00:14:47,867 --> 00:14:49,801
Excuse me, please.

200
00:15:00,813 --> 00:15:02,246
You going out?

201
00:15:02,315 --> 00:15:03,748
Mm-hmm.

202
00:15:03,816 --> 00:15:05,249
Early, isn't it?

203
00:15:05,318 --> 00:15:08,287
I want to make
happy hour.

204
00:15:08,354 --> 00:15:10,288
Want to come along?

205
00:15:11,857 --> 00:15:15,258
No. I think
I'll stay home tonight.

206
00:15:15,328 --> 00:15:16,761
No kidding.

207
00:15:16,829 --> 00:15:18,262
What's that mean?

208
00:15:18,331 --> 00:15:20,356
It means, no kidding.

209
00:15:20,433 --> 00:15:23,266
I don't feel like
going out.

210
00:15:23,336 --> 00:15:26,271
He never feels like
doing anything.

211
00:15:26,339 --> 00:15:27,772
That's not true.

212
00:15:27,840 --> 00:15:30,104
Every night it's the same.

213
00:15:30,176 --> 00:15:33,043
He listens to that crap.

214
00:15:33,112 --> 00:15:36,775
That crap happens
to be George Gershwin.

215
00:15:36,849 --> 00:15:39,784
It's like I'm not even here.

216
00:15:39,885 --> 00:15:43,821
He's like a turtle
hiding in his shell.

217
00:15:43,889 --> 00:15:47,593
He hasn't taken off
those sunglasses in six years.

218
00:15:47,593 --> 00:15:49,060
He hasn't taken off
those sunglasses in six years.

219
00:15:49,128 --> 00:15:53,064
I've given up trying
to figure him out.

220
00:15:57,803 --> 00:16:00,670
Maybe you should take him
back to Vietnam.

221
00:16:00,740 --> 00:16:04,699
He doesn't give a damn
about anything here.

222
00:16:04,777 --> 00:16:07,712
It was nice meeting
you, Colonel.

223
00:16:07,780 --> 00:16:09,213
Nice meeting you.

224
00:16:13,286 --> 00:16:14,719
If he did go,

225
00:16:14,787 --> 00:16:17,722
how much
would he be paid?

226
00:16:17,790 --> 00:16:19,223
Nothing in dollars.

227
00:16:33,272 --> 00:16:36,708
I haven't flown a helicopter
in a while.

228
00:16:36,809 --> 00:16:39,300
I'd probably get
somebody killed.

229
00:16:39,412 --> 00:16:43,041
There's unfinished business
over there, MajorJohnson.

230
00:16:43,149 --> 00:16:44,639
Not mine.

231
00:16:47,820 --> 00:16:49,754
Is this the Distinguished
Flying Cross?

232
00:16:49,822 --> 00:16:51,255
Yeah.

233
00:16:51,324 --> 00:16:52,757
How'd you get that?

234
00:16:52,825 --> 00:16:57,228
Ah...pulling a cub pilot
out of Laos.

235
00:16:57,296 --> 00:16:59,389
Must have been
more to it than that.

236
00:16:59,465 --> 00:17:00,625
Not really.

237
00:17:00,700 --> 00:17:05,160
Tell me about it.
I'd like to hear it.

238
00:17:05,237 --> 00:17:06,670
I got him out

239
00:17:06,739 --> 00:17:10,175
after a lot of good people
went down trying.

240
00:17:10,276 --> 00:17:13,211
It was a hell ofa day.

241
00:17:13,279 --> 00:17:15,713
We'd already lost
a good man named Hendricks,

242
00:17:15,781 --> 00:17:17,715
couple of F-4jocks,

243
00:17:17,783 --> 00:17:19,717
even Sandy Low Lead.

244
00:17:19,785 --> 00:17:22,720
Lost a lot of good friends.

245
00:17:22,788 --> 00:17:24,380
How many?

246
00:17:24,457 --> 00:17:26,220
Oh, I don't remember.

247
00:17:26,292 --> 00:17:28,192
It just seemed
like everybody.

248
00:17:28,260 --> 00:17:30,524
You lost 11 men
and 9 aircraft.

249
00:17:30,596 --> 00:17:34,191
You were shot down,
and you went back.

250
00:17:34,266 --> 00:17:35,324
Why?

251
00:17:35,401 --> 00:17:37,392
If you know that,
you tell me.

252
00:17:37,470 --> 00:17:38,767
Why?

253
00:17:38,838 --> 00:17:40,066
It was my job!

254
00:17:40,139 --> 00:17:41,071
Right!

255
00:17:41,140 --> 00:17:44,268
We couldn't let good men
die for nothing!

256
00:17:44,377 --> 00:17:47,369
That's why we're
going back now.

257
00:17:47,480 --> 00:17:48,708
Wait! Back up!

258
00:17:48,814 --> 00:17:51,749
Don't lay that guilt on me!

259
00:17:51,817 --> 00:17:53,250
No!

260
00:17:53,319 --> 00:17:56,755
I'm sorry,
but the answer is no.

261
00:17:59,325 --> 00:18:02,158
What do you
want from me?

262
00:18:02,228 --> 00:18:04,662
I run half this hospital.

263
00:18:04,730 --> 00:18:07,665
I'm off to Bermuda
next week

264
00:18:07,733 --> 00:18:11,169
and not off
to some fantasy war.

265
00:18:11,237 --> 00:18:14,172
I cannot save
the goddamn world!

266
00:18:14,240 --> 00:18:15,673
At ease, Major.

267
00:18:17,943 --> 00:18:19,171
[Telephone Rings]

268
00:18:19,278 --> 00:18:20,711
MacGregor Oil.

269
00:18:20,780 --> 00:18:22,213
Mr. MacGregor, please.

270
00:18:22,281 --> 00:18:23,714
Mr. MacGregor's office.

271
00:18:23,783 --> 00:18:26,217
This is Jason Rhodes
