in his letters.

297
00:19:45,965 --> 00:19:48,695
He said you were
the best man in the unit.

298
00:19:48,767 --> 00:19:49,699
Yeah?

299
00:19:49,768 --> 00:19:52,202
What the hell
happened to you?

300
00:19:55,274 --> 00:19:58,732
I'm so far beyond
that shit now.

301
00:19:58,811 --> 00:20:00,745
I get energy
from the air.

302
00:20:00,813 --> 00:20:04,249
I talk to polar bears.
I converse with paramecium.

303
00:20:04,316 --> 00:20:06,750
Man, I fuck nuclear waste!

304
00:20:08,654 --> 00:20:09,746
Shit.

305
00:20:14,793 --> 00:20:18,229
You guys will be
using real grenades.

306
00:20:18,297 --> 00:20:20,060
They took mine.

307
00:20:20,132 --> 00:20:21,565
Hey, look, asshole.

308
00:20:21,634 --> 00:20:25,070
This is not
a bikers' acid trip.

309
00:20:25,137 --> 00:20:28,072
This is a precise
military operation.

310
00:20:28,140 --> 00:20:32,099
Frank was the best man
in anybody's unit.

311
00:20:32,177 --> 00:20:36,113
I've got enough brain cells
to remember that.

312
00:20:38,350 --> 00:20:42,286
You've got to
give me a shot, man.

313
00:20:42,354 --> 00:20:43,787
You've got to.

314
00:20:46,692 --> 00:20:48,125
Hey, Wilkesy.

315
00:20:52,665 --> 00:20:54,098
Come on, man.

316
00:20:59,171 --> 00:21:00,695
Sailor?

317
00:21:00,773 --> 00:21:02,206
Ya-hoo!

318
00:21:05,311 --> 00:21:06,744
My master!

319
00:21:08,814 --> 00:21:11,248
You haven't changed a bit!

320
00:21:11,317 --> 00:21:12,750
Master Wilkes!

321
00:21:12,818 --> 00:21:14,251
Where's your grenade?

322
00:21:14,320 --> 00:21:17,551
