I won't fail in combat.

364
00:24:04,757 --> 00:24:08,158
But you can't prove
that I will.

365
00:24:10,062 --> 00:24:11,996
This is gonna be

366
00:24:12,064 --> 00:24:16,000
a whole lot offun
with this one.

367
00:24:17,269 --> 00:24:18,497
Gentlemen.

368
00:24:21,273 --> 00:24:23,207
Thankyou for coming.

369
00:24:23,275 --> 00:24:26,210
I knew you would come,

370
00:24:26,278 --> 00:24:30,214
'cause you men
have got what it takes.

371
00:24:30,282 --> 00:24:32,216
Molded over a little,

372
00:24:32,284 --> 00:24:34,718
but you still got it.

373
00:24:35,788 --> 00:24:38,723
There's a bond
between you men

374
00:24:38,791 --> 00:24:43,694
as strong as the bond
between my son and me.

375
00:24:43,762 --> 00:24:47,198
Of course, men who faced
death in battle

376
00:24:47,266 --> 00:24:49,200
share the strongest bond.

377
00:24:49,301 --> 00:24:54,238
You men seem to have
a strong sense of loyalty

378
00:24:54,306 --> 00:24:57,241
because you're thought
of as criminals

379
00:24:57,309 --> 00:24:58,742
because of Vietnam.

380
00:24:58,811 --> 00:25:00,403
You know why?

381
00:25:02,748 --> 00:25:04,181
Because you lost.

382
00:25:04,249 --> 00:25:06,683
And in this country,

383
00:25:06,752 --> 00:25:08,686
that's like
going bankrupt.

384
00:25:08,754 --> 00:25:10,688
You're out of business.

385
00:25:10,756 --> 00:25:13,691
They want to forget
about you.

386
00:25:13,759 --> 00:25:15,659
You cost too much

387
00:25:15,727 --> 00:25:18,161
and didn't turn a profit.

388
00:25:18,230 --> 00:25:21,666
That's why they
won't get our buddies.

389
00:25:21,733 --> 00:25:24,167
There's no gain in it.

390
00:25:24,269 --> 00:25:28,706
We know the books
are still in the red.

391
00:25:28,774 --> 00:25:30,708
The politicians know, too.

392
00:25:30,776 --> 00:25:32,209
The same politicians

393
00:25:32,277 --> 00:25:35,713
that never lost a son
in Vietnam.

394
00:25:35,781 --> 00:25:39,217
They say they've
negotiated for 10 years.

395
00:25:39,284 --> 00:25:40,717
Well...

396
00:25:42,287 --> 00:25:44,721
the other side's
not buying.

397
00:25:46,291 --> 00:25:50,193
And while the politicians
sit on their asses,

398
00:25:50,262 --> 00:25:54,528
I'm asking you
to lay yours on the line.

399
00:25:54,600 --> 00:25:55,726
Again.

400
00:25:58,303 --> 00:25:59,998
Because, gentlemen...

401
00:26:01,740 --> 00:26:05,176
we're the only hope
those P.O.W.s have.

402
00:26:06,845 --> 00:26:09,177
So, we're going
back there.

403
00:26:10,382 --> 00:26:12,179
And this time...

404
00:26:12,251 --> 00:26:14,685
this time,
nobody can dispute

405
00:26:14,753 --> 00:26:18,189
the rightness
of what we're doing.

406
00:26:32,271 --> 00:26:33,704
Get down!

407
00:26:34,773 --> 00:26:36,206
You're all dead.

408
00:26:37,276 --> 00:26:38,709
