woman and her kid.

464
00:30:23,735 --> 00:30:26,169
Killed them
deader than shit.

465
00:30:26,271 --> 00:30:27,704
Jesus.

466
00:30:27,772 --> 00:30:29,205
Wilkes starts freaking.

467
00:30:29,274 --> 00:30:31,708
We can hear him
screaming,

468
00:30:31,776 --> 00:30:35,212
but he has to stay
with those corpses

469
00:30:35,280 --> 00:30:37,714
until we dig him out.

470
00:30:39,217 --> 00:30:42,948
You come in low
under his line of sight.

471
00:30:45,290 --> 00:30:46,723
You leap...

472
00:30:46,791 --> 00:30:48,190
taking him down,

473
00:30:48,260 --> 00:30:51,195
placing your hand
over his nose,

474
00:30:51,263 --> 00:30:53,197
pulling his face away.

475
00:30:53,265 --> 00:30:56,200
At the base of his skull,

476
00:30:56,268 --> 00:30:58,532
you insert,
scramble the brains--

477
00:30:58,637 --> 00:31:00,537
Instant rag doll.

478
00:31:00,605 --> 00:31:03,130
Most human problems
can be solved

479
00:31:03,241 --> 00:31:05,675
by a charge
of high explosive.

480
00:31:05,744 --> 00:31:07,177
In today's lesson,

481
00:31:07,245 --> 00:31:10,180
we'll learn to set a series.

482
00:31:10,248 --> 00:31:11,681
Follow me.

483
00:31:11,750 --> 00:31:16,847
The idea is to create
a linked series of disasters.

484
00:31:16,922 --> 00:31:19,516
Figure evasive moves
from each blast,

485
00:31:19,591 --> 00:31:21,991
and plant
your next tomato.

486
00:31:22,060 --> 00:31:24,995
Just as we're
coming up here,

487
00:31:25,063 --> 00:31:27,497
they'd trip
charge number one.

488
00:31:27,566 --> 00:31:28,658
Boom!

489
00:31:28,733 --> 00:31:30,667
Column splits in two.

490
00:31:30,735 --> 00:31:32,703
Half here, half there.

491
00:31:32,771 --> 00:31:36,207
Over here, number two
will set their ass on fire.

492
00:31:36,274 --> 00:31:39,209
They think they're safe.
They get away!

493
00:31:39,277 --> 00:31:43,577
Boom! Number three
blows their balls off.

494
00:31:43,648 --> 00:31:46,208
Number four!
They come over here.

495
00:31:46,284 --> 00:31:49,219
They find
a two-pound charge.

496
00:31:49,287 --> 00:31:50,720
Boom!

497
00:31:50,789 --> 00:31:52,222
Number five.

498
00:31:52,290 --> 00:31:53,723
Quick fuse grenade.

499
00:31:53,792 --> 00:31:58,195
Not a big bang,
but it does a good job.

500
00:31:58,263 --> 00:32:02,632
Anybody left will think,
"We've got to make it."

501
00:32:02,701 --> 00:32:06,660
They're coming out
and run into charge six.

502
00:32:06,738 --> 00:32:09,002
Claymore mine.
End of story.

503
00:32:20,252 --> 00:32:23,346
Congratulations, Sailor.
You wasted a prisoner.

504
00:32:25,257 --> 00:32:26,690
He's a collaborator.

505
00:32:35,734 --> 00:32:37,167
You all right?

506
00:32:42,907 --> 00:32:45,171
Can't sleep, huh?

507
00:32:50,782 --> 00:32:54,218
Foryears, I couldn't sleep
after Korea.

508
00:32:54,286 --> 00:32:57,722
